## Other Annotations

 * *[definition](../../IAO/15/IAO_0000115.md)* = A urethral meatus that is part of a female urethra[Automatically generated definition].
 * *[external_definition](../../UBPROP/01/UBPROP_0000001.md)* = The external urethral orifice (urinary meatus) is the external opening of the urethra, from which urine is ejected during urination. It is placed about 2.5 cm behind the glans clitoridis and immediately in front of that of the vagina; it usually assumes the form of a short, sagittal cleft with slightly raised margins. To its left and right are the openings of the Skene's ducts.
